wikipedia_page.main: Edward Heneage (21 July 1775 – 7 October 1810) was an English first-class cricketer who was active in the 1790s playing for Surrey. He is recorded in one first-class match in 1796, totalling 3 runs with a highest score of 3.Heneage was born in London and died in Lisbon, aged 35, during the Peninsular War.

response: *Edward Heneage, 1st Baron Heneage (1840–1922), British politician, MP for Grimsby and Lincoln, nephew of the above
